<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-30T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-30T19:36:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/300: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-30T18:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                            1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        August 1, 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Prof. Kemmerer and assistant arrived Guatemala July 20. He was
                                immediately received by President Cabrera and now informs me his
                                [progress] to date quite satisfactory.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>